# Planning new work

When proposing a plan that **builds something new** (features, major refactors, new integrations), include all of the following.

## 1. New domain objects

For each object: **role** (quest, adventurer, weapon, skill_book, item, etc.), **code home** (exact path pattern under `libs/` / `app/`), **data home** (DB tables vs code-only).

## 2. Modules to add or reuse

Files to create or extend (JavaScript/TypeScript modules — not the in-world “class” concept). Name exports and dependencies.

## 3. Surfaces

API routes, server actions, UI, env vars, auth.

## 4. Migrations and RLS

Whether the schema changes; follow `database-migrations.mdc` (`.cursor/rules/`) and put SQL in `supabase/migrations/` (Supabase CLI).

Optional: short mermaid diagram for multi-step flows.
